ratiometric fluorescence sensor could present vivid dosage-dependent fluorescence color changes, which is more easily semi-qualitatively recognized Hg2+ by the naked eye. Therefore, the ratiometric fluorescence method based on N, S-CDs/Ru nanocomposites was feasible to determine Hg2+. Notably, the light-yellow suspensions faded and became transparent, accompanied with abundant fluffy precipitate produced during the increasing of Hg2+ concentration process (especially [Hg2+] ≥16.0 μM)(
                        Fig. S4
                        ). It implied that a large amount of Hg2+ adsorption by N, S-CDs/Ru nanocomposites due to the powerful binding force between nanocomposites and Hg2+ occurred also promising the removal of Hg2+ from environmental water.
